Note:
Comprehensive test suite for the Net module

Tests cover:
- Socket operations (TCP, UDP, Unix)
- HTTP client/server functionality
- WebSocket operations
- SSL/TLS security
- Network discovery and monitoring
- Error handling and edge cases
- Performance and load testing
- Security testing
:End Note

Note: Test socket creation and basic operations
:End Note

Let test_socket_creation:
    Let tcp_socket be create tcp socket
    Assert tcp_socket is not empty
    
    Let udp_socket be create udp socket
    Assert udp_socket is not empty
    
    Let unix_socket be create unix socket
    Assert unix_socket is not empty
    
    Note: Test socket with type parameter
    Let socket be create socket with type as "tcp"
    Assert socket is not empty
End

Let test_socket_binding:
    Let socket be create tcp socket
    Let bound be bind socket to "localhost" on port 0
    Assert bound is true
    
    Let socket_info be get socket info socket
    Assert socket_info is not empty
End

Let test_socket_connection:
    Let server_socket be create tcp socket
    Let bound be bind socket to "localhost" on port 0
    Let listening be listen socket with backlog 1
    
    If listening is true:
        Let client_socket be create tcp socket
        Let connected be connect socket to "localhost" on port 0
        
        If connected is true:
            Let server_conn be accept connection from server_socket
            Assert server_conn is not empty
            
            Close server_conn
        End If
        
        Close client_socket
    End If
    
    Close server_socket
End

Let test_socket_data_transfer:
    Let server_socket be create tcp socket
    Let bound be bind socket to "localhost" on port 0
    Let listening be listen socket with backlog 1
    
    If listening is true:
        Let client_socket be create tcp socket
        Let connected be connect socket to "localhost" on port 0
        
        If connected is true:
            Let server_conn be accept connection from server_socket
            
            Let test_message be "Hello, Network!"
            Let sent be send data through client_socket with test_message
            Assert sent is greater than 0
            
            Let received be receive data from server_conn with buffer size 1024
            Assert received equals test_message
            
            Let response be "Hello, Client!"
            Let sent_response be send data through server_conn with response
            Assert sent_response is greater than 0
            
            Let received_response be receive data from client_socket with buffer size 1024
            Assert received_response equals response
            
            Close server_conn
        End If
        
        Close client_socket
    End If
    
    Close server_socket
End

Let test_socket_binary_transfer:
    Let server_socket be create tcp socket
    Let bound be bind socket to "localhost" on port 0
    Let listening be listen socket with backlog 1
    
    If listening is true:
        Let client_socket be create tcp socket
        Let connected be connect socket to "localhost" on port 0
        
        If connected is true:
            Let server_conn be accept connection from server_socket
            
            Let test_data be [72, 101, 108, 108, 111]  Note: "Hello" in ASCII
            Let sent be send bytes through client_socket with test_data
            Assert sent equals 5
            
            Let received be receive bytes from server_conn with buffer size 1024
            Assert received equals test_data
            
            Close server_conn
        End If
        
        Close client_socket
    End If
    
    Close server_socket
End

Let test_socket_options:
    Let socket be create tcp socket
    
    Let timeout_set be set socket timeout socket with 5.0
    Assert timeout_set is true
    
    Let reuse_set be set socket reuse address socket with true
    Assert reuse_set is true
    
    Let keepalive_set be set socket keepalive socket with true
    Assert keepalive_set is true
    
    Let nodelay_set be set socket nodelay socket with true
    Assert nodelay_set is true
    
    Close socket
End

Let test_socket_addresses:
    Let server_socket be create tcp socket
    Let bound be bind socket to "localhost" on port 0
    Let listening be listen socket with backlog 1
    
    If listening is true:
        Let client_socket be create tcp socket
        Let connected be connect socket to "localhost" on port 0
        
        If connected is true:
            Let server_conn be accept connection from server_socket
            
            Let peer_addr be get peer address server_conn
            Assert peer_addr is not empty
            
            Let local_addr be get local address server_conn
            Assert local_addr is not empty
            
            Close server_conn
        End If
        
        Close client_socket
    End If
    
    Close server_socket
End

Note: Test network discovery functions
:End Note

Let test_hostname_resolution:
    Let ips be resolve hostname "localhost"
    Assert ips is not empty
    Assert "127.0.0.1" is in ips
    
    Let hostname be resolve ip "127.0.0.1"
    Assert hostname is not empty
End

Let test_network_interfaces:
    Let interfaces be get network interfaces
    Assert interfaces is not empty
    
    For each interface in interfaces:
        Assert interface contains "name"
        Assert interface contains "addresses"
    End For
End

Let test_interface_addresses:
    Let interfaces be get network interfaces
    
    If interfaces is not empty:
        Let first_interface be interfaces[0]
        Let interface_name be first_interface["name"]
        
        Let addresses be get interface addresses interface_name
        Assert addresses is not empty
    End If
End

Let test_network_utilities:
    Let gateway be get default gateway
    Assert gateway is not empty
    
    Let dns_servers be get dns servers
    Assert dns_servers is not empty
    
    Let ping_result be ping host "localhost"
    Assert ping_result is not empty
    Assert ping_result contains "success"
End

Let test_port_operations:
    Let port_open be check port "localhost" on port 80
    Note: Port 80 may or may not be open, so we just test the function call
    
    Let scanned_ports be scan ports "localhost" from 80 to 85
    Assert scanned_ports is not empty
End

Note: Test HTTP client operations
:End Note

Let test_http_client_creation:
    Let client be create http client
    Assert client is not empty
End

Let test_http_client_configuration:
    Let client be create http client
    
    Set http headers for client to {"User-Agent": "Runa-Test/1.0"}
    Set http timeout for client to 30.0
    Set http ssl verify for client to false
    
    Note: Test configuration was applied
End

Let test_http_requests:
    Let client be create http client
    
    Note: Test GET request to a test server
    Let response be http get "http://httpbin.org/get"
    Assert response is not empty
    
    Let status be get http response status from response
    Assert status is 200
    
    Let headers be get http response headers from response
    Assert headers is not empty
    
    Let body be get http response body from response
    Assert body is not empty
End

Let test_http_post_request:
    Let client be create http client
    
    Let post_data be '{"test": "data"}'
    Let response be http post "http://httpbin.org/post" with post_data
    
    Assert response is not empty
    Let status be get http response status from response
    Assert status is 200
End

Let test_http_custom_request:
    Let client be create http client
    
    Let headers be {"Content-Type": "application/json"}
    Let data be '{"method": "test"}'
    Let response be http request "POST" to "http://httpbin.org/anything" with headers and data
    
    Assert response is not empty
    Let status be get http response status from response
    Assert status is 200
End

